Traditional Ad Agencies have been king of the marketing world for years. But in today's society with technology continuing to advance along with our consumers, are these traditional agencies keeping up?

In my opinion, no. With the rise of consulting and freelancing, traditional agencies are falling behind because they aren't willing to adapt, or should I say adapt at the pace that they should.

These agencies aren't willing to give up the traditional marketing that got them to where they currently are...but if they don't catch up with the times, they won't survive.

The problem with most agencies is that they think they are kings/queens of the advertising world. But again, it's these small companies, startups and individuals that are continuing to push the limits and change the game of advertising.

Traditional agencies are no longer at the top, UNLESS they decide to set aside their ego and adapt.

Toyota Owners Event at Cihan Motors - Fleet Customers, 15th of May 
On 15th May, 2017, Cihan Motors conducted the Toyota Owners' Event for its Fleet Customers (UN Agencies, Consulates, NGOs , Representative Government and Private Companies), at  Duhok Showroom. Officials and representatives from various organizations participated in the Event, in the presence of Toyota Distributor Organization, in which Cihan Motors briefed its 3S facilities - Sales, Service & Spare Parts, and gave an overview of its Group Business and Cihan Motors automobiles operations. Senior officials from Cihan Motors responded to the questions and suggestions by some of the invited officials.
